{"author":{"id":"f270607f232f5ea3e06daa2368d41de7674a6d0d64158946f2581dde2c4881fc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774025599,"nonce":"QzsDsFrXRnrFrXpsKz74EKkFa64=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s706ahu","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7807","origin":"github"},"title":"Trimmomatic: detection of quality encoding","message":"The Trimmomatic wrapper has the optional param: *\"Quality score encoding\"*, where the default is to auto-detect the encoding from the input.\nThis auto-detection is fragile and has failed users occasionally. At the same time, we have dedicated datatypes (fastqsanger and fastqillumina) for the two param options phred+33 and phred+64 so when the input is of any of these two types, it's Galaxy that can decide for the user.\nIt's probably best to remove this parameter altogether and explicitly use `-phred33` for fastqsanger (and, I guess, fastq, too) and `-phred64` for fastqillumina.\nThe tool  wrapper doesn't seem to be the right place to declare the encoding, but the datatype is.","files":null}]}